The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 Hyderabad, July 31 (PTI): Two training instructors of the Air Force Academy at Dundigal in Hyderabad were killed when their aircraft crashed today.           Jain and N. Chaturvedi, both 32, were killed on the spot when their HPT-32 training aircraft crashed on a ground about 1km from the academy. The plane crashed while trying to land at the academy at 9.45am, district superintendent of police M. Kanta Rao said.           
	The crash occurred reportedly because of a technical snag, another officer said. The Indian Air Force has ordered an inquiry. A medical branch of the IAF would collect body samples from the spot for post-mortem.                   
	 Chennai: The Supreme Court has ordered the demolition of an arch built on a highway to mark Jayalalithaas birthday. The court set aside an order by the Jayalalithaa government giving permission for two arches on the highway.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): The Central Information Commission has ruled that political parties are not covered under the Right to Information Act. A man who had been refused certain information by 12 political parties had filed an RTI application. But the panel ruled that the act couldnt cover political parties just because they are provided government subsidies relating to and media coverage.                  
	 Kanpur (PTI): IIT Kanpur will start a radio station to broadcast scientific programmes and classical music.                                                                                                                            
